###################################################################
####Extract standardized beta coefficients from linear mixed models
###################################################################
stdCoef.merMod <- function(object) {
  sdy <- sd(getME(object,"y"))
  sdx <- apply(getME(object,"X"), 2, sd)
  sc <- fixef(object)*sdx/sdy
  se.fixef <- coef(summary(object))[,"Std. Error"]
  se <- se.fixef*sdx/sdy
  return(data.frame(stdcoef=sc, stdse=se))
}

####################################
###Reshape dataset from wide to long
####################################
pain.data.long = melt(pain.data.time, measure.vars=repeated.variables, 
                       variable.name = "day", value.name = "pain_rating")

pain.data.long = pain.data.long[order(pain.data.long[,"ID"]),]

View(pain.data.long)

pain.data.long$day <- as.numeric(pain.data.long$day) 


######################################################
###Creating a mixed linear model with random intercept
######################################################
model.int <- lmer(pain_rating ~ sex + age + weight + STAI_trait + pain_cat + mindfulness + cortisol_serum
                  + day + (1|ID), data = pain.data.long)

#####################################################
###Creating a model with random intercept and slope
#####################################################
model.slope <- lmer(pain_rating ~ sex + age + weight + STAI_trait + pain_cat + mindfulness + cortisol_serum
                  + day  + (day|ID), data = pain.data.long)

########################################################################
###Create a copy of dataset that can be used for predicting and plotting
########################################################################
pain.data.long.withpreds = pain.data.long
pain.data.long.withpreds$pred.int = predict(model.int)
pain.data.long.withpreds$pred.slope = predict(model.slope)


################################################
###Plot the two models with randomm intercept and slope
################################################

###############################################################
###Create a new randome slope model with day as a quadratic term
################################################################
model.slope.quad <- lmer(pain_rating ~ sex + age + weight + STAI_trait + pain_cat + mindfulness + cortisol_serum
                          + day + I(day^2) +(day^2|ID), data = pain.data.long)


#####################################################
###GGplot for the new slope model with quadratic term
#####################################################
pain.data.long.withpreds$pred.slope.quad = predict(model.slope.quad)

windows()
ggplot(pain.data.long.withpreds, aes(y = pain_rating, x = day, group = ID))+
  geom_point(size = 3)+
  geom_line(color='green', aes(y=pred.slope.quad, x=day))+
  facet_wrap( ~ ID, ncol = 5)

#######################################################################
###Center varible "day" to avoid multicollinearity with the quadtric term
#######################################################################
pain.data.long.centered.day = pain.data.long
pain.data.long.centered.day$day.centered = pain.data.long.centered.day$day -
  mean(pain.data.long.centered.day$day)
pain.data.long.centered.day$day.centered.2 = pain.data.long.centered.day$day.centered^2

model.slope.quad <- lmer(pain_rating ~ sex + age + weight + STAI_trait + pain_cat + mindfulness + cortisol_serum
                          + day.centered + I(day.centered^2) +(day.centered^2|ID), 
                          data = pain.data.long.centered.day)

# caluclate interquartile range within each cluster
IQR.of.residuals.by.participant = sapply(split(pain.data.long.with.resid, f = pain.data.long.with.resid$ID), function(x) IQR(x$resid))
# rank ordering them
rank = rank(IQR.of.residuals.by.participant)
# adding rank to the dataframe containing the residuals
pain.data.long.with.resid$rank = rep(rank, each = length(repeated.variables))
# creating a vector of participant IDs ordered based on the rank, this will be used as labels
IDforplot = unique(pain.data.long.with.resid$ID[order(pain.data.long.with.resid$rank)])

# create the cyclone plot
ggplot(pain.data.long.with.resid, aes(y = resid, x = factor(rank), labels = ID))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  scale_x_discrete(labels=IDforplot)+
  coord_flip()
